-- Bank of America Earnings Beat Estimates as Pressure From Bad Loans Abates
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-07-16T11:00:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/bank-of-america-earnings-beat-estimates-as-pressure-from-bad-loans-abates.html

          
          
             Bank of America Corp. reported a
second-quarter profit of 27 cents a share.  
 The average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was
a profit of 23 cents a share.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Bank of America Corp chief executive officer Brian T. Moynihan. Photographer: Chris Keane/Bloomberg  
                           

     
